<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='640000' id='t-640000'>and World of Warcraft has quite a budget.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='642000' id='t-642000'>Most of the educational games do not.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='644000' id='t-644000'>Where we started:</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='646000' id='t-646000'>my colleagues -- Mike Petner, Shawn Vashaw, myself --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='649000' id='t-649000'>we started by trying to look at the teachers' attitudes</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='651000' id='t-651000'>and find out how do they really feel about gaming,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='653000' id='t-653000'>what do they say about it.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='655000' id='t-655000'>And we discovered</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='657000' id='t-657000'>that they talk about the kids in their school,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='659000' id='t-659000'>who talk about gaming,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='661000' id='t-661000'>in pretty demeaning ways.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='663000' id='t-663000'>They say, &quot;Oh, yeah. They're always talking about that stuff.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='666000' id='t-666000'>They're talking about their little action figures</span>
